cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.CE

This paper is about multi-path routing in mobile ad hoc networks, which is a topic related to network protocols and communication in computer networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes an analytical framework based on graph theory, which involves mathematical modeling and analysis, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of multi-path routing protocols, which can be related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper evaluates the reliability of multi-path routing, which can be related to computer engineering (cs.CE).
